---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About">
	<div class="about-container">
		<div class="header">
			<h1>Independent Social Worker | Child Protection Consultant</h1>
		</div>
		
		<div class="content">
			<p>
				Debbie Allen is an independent social worker with a specialised focus on child protection
				and child sexual abuse prevention. Through her work, she provides services in risk
				assessments, capacity-to-protect assessments, training, and consultation, all aimed at
				enhancing safety and well-being for vulnerable children and families.
			</p>
			
			<p>
				Debbie is highly skilled in using both actuarial and dynamic risk assessment tools, including
				Aim3, Stable and Acute 2007, and Risk Matrix 2000. These tools allow her to provide
				comprehensive and evidence-based assessments that support safety planning and guide
				effective interventions. Her approach includes evaluating both static (actuarial) and evolving
				(dynamic) risk factors, ensuring a thorough understanding of potential risks and protective
				factors in child protection cases.
			</p>
			
			<p>
				In addition to risk assessments, Debbie conducts Capacity and Ability to Supervise and
				Protect -Risk framework (CASP-r) assessments, evaluating the ability of parents and carers
				to maintain a protective environment. Her work forms the foundation for creating tailored
				safety plans that are responsive to the unique needs of each case.
			</p>
			
			<p>
				Debbie also offers consultation and training to a wide range of professionals, including social
				workers and individuals in the voluntary sector. Her training programmes focus on enhancing
				the use of risk assessment tools, developing effective safety strategies, and strengthening
				collaboration across sectors. Debbie is committed to building the capacity of professionals to
				manage complex child protection and sexual abuse prevention cases with expertise and
				confidence.
			</p>
			
			<p>
				With a trauma-informed, child-centred approach, Debbie's work aims to empower
				professionals, ensure effective protective measures, and ultimately promote safer
				environments for children at risk.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		<div class="cta">
			<a href="/contact" class="cta-button">Get in Touch</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.about-container {
		padding: 2rem 0;
	}

	.header {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
		font-weight: 500;
		line-height: 1.2;
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
	}

	.content {
		max-width: 800px;
	}

	p {
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.2vw, 1.1rem);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.cta {
		margin-top: 3rem;
	}

	.cta-button {
		display: inline-block;
		background-color: var(--color-primary);
		color: var(--color-text);
		text-decoration: none;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
		font-weight: 500;
		transition: background-color 0.2s;
	}

	.cta-button:hover {
		background-color: #d35400;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.about-container {
			padding: 1rem 0;
		}
		
		.header {
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}
	}
</style>

<style>
	:root {
		--color-primary: #e67e22;
		--color-text: #ffffff;
	}

	* {
		margin: 0;
		padding: 0;
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	body {
		font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
		color: var(--color-text);
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.container {
		min-height: 100vh;
		background: linear-gradient(rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6), rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6)), url('/background.jpg');
		background-size: cover;
		background-position: center;
	}

	nav {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
	}

	.logo {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	.logo img {
		height: 2rem;
	}

	.nav-links {
		display: flex;
		gap: 2rem;
	}

	.nav-links a {
		color: var(--color-text);
		text-decoration: none;
		font-size: 1rem;
		transition: opacity 0.2s;
	}

	.nav-links a:hover {
		opacity: 0.8;
	}

	.get-in-touch {
		background-color: var(--color-primary);
		color: var(--color-text);
		border: none;
		padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 4px;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-weight: 500;
		transition: background-color 0.2s;
	}

	.get-in-touch:hover {
		background-color: #d35400;
	}

	main {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 6rem 2rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
		font-weight: 500;
		line-height: 1.2;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	p {
		max-width: 600px;
		font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.25rem);
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	.scroll-indicator {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		opacity: 0.8;
		animation: bounce 2s infinite;
	}

	.arrow-down {
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}

	@keyframes bounce {
		0%, 20%, 50%, 80%, 100% {
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
		40% {
			transform: translateY(-10px);
		}
		60% {
			transform: translateY(-5px);
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.nav-links {
			display: none;
		}

		main {
			padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
		}
	}
</style>
